## The part that caused the vulnerability

- Yes, I finally found the problem.

You can log in or out of your account,

but if there is an address in the "?logout=url" url in the address section, you will not receive the request to log out or login and you will be redirected directly, which is more problematic than the others, we redirect as if we were redirecting to our own site.

- so you won't be able to receive a request called "/user/logout", but if you type a normal word, the request will come,

problem for sure "?" It is in the logout parameter that comes after the sign. this parameter should not be changed, or the logout parameter should be deleted when exiting. It should not affect the address bar in any way.

